STEPS

1. create package.json - npm init
2. create nodemodules - install express -  npm i express
3. create index.js file
4. import express inside the index.js
5. using express create an app
6. setup port number 
7. Use json parser for server application 
8. Install cors -  npm i cors
9. import cors
10.using cors specify origin to the server (integration)
11. API fetch - search in google : fakestoreapi/products
12. create db and collection in mongo db compass
13.Install mongoose to establish connection between server and mongodb
14. Create a folder services and create 2 files db.js, dataService.js
15.in db.js - import mongoose to establish connection
16. define connection string
17. create model and schema
18. Export model
19. import db in dataService, create a function and export it.
20. Resolving API request in index.js 
  index + dataService
  Node + MongoDB connection Successfull
21. Final Step
//Api to get all products
